This paper is primarily focused on face image generation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) also suggests that it could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions multimedia research, which could place it under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the proposed method involves regularization, which could suggest a connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
